element.name: dcat:accessService

element.name: dcat:endpointURL

element.description: The root location or primary endpoint of the service (a Web-resolvable IRI).

element.name: dcat:hadRole

element.description: The function of an entity or agent with respect to another entity or resource.

element.name: dcat:keyword
element.label: Keyword
element.description: A keyword or tag describing the resource.

element.name: dcat:landingPage
element.label: Landing page
element.description: A Web page that can be navigated to in a Web browser to gain access to the catalog, a dataset, its distributions and/or additional information.

element.name: dcat:mediaType
element.label: Media type
element.description: The media type of the distribution as defined by IANA.

element.name: dcat:packageFormat
element.label: Package format
element.description: The package format of the distribution in which one or more data files are grouped together, e.g. to enable a set of related files to be downloaded together.

element.name: dcat:qualifiedRelation
element.label: Qualified relation
element.description: Link to a description of a relationship with another resource

element.name: dcat:servesDataset
element.label: Serves dataset
element.description: A collection of data that this data service can distribute.

element.name: dcat:spatialResolutionInMeters
element.label: Spatial resolution in meters
element.description: Minimum spatial separation resolvable in a dataset, measured in meters.

element.name: dcat:temporalResolution
element.label: Temporal resolution
element.description: Minimum time period resolvable in the dataset.

element.name: dcat:theme
element.label: Theme
element.description: A main category of the resource. A resource can have multiple themes.

element.name: dct:LicenseDocument

element.name: dct:Location
element.label: Location

element.name: dct:PeriodOfTime

element.description: An interval of time that is named or defined by its start and end.

element.name: dct:RightsStatement
element.label: Rights statement
element.description: A statement about the intellectual property rights (IPR) held in or over a resource, a legal document giving official permission to do something with a resource, or a statement about access rights.

element.name: dct:Standard
element.label: Standard
element.description: A reference point against which other things can be evaluated or compared.

element.name: dct:accessRights
element.label: Access rights
element.description: Information about who can access the resource or an indication of its security status.

element.name: dct:accrualPeriodicity
element.label: Frequency
element.description: The frequency with which items are added to a collection.

element.name: dct:conformsTo
element.label: Conforms to standard
element.description: An established standard to which the described resource conforms.

element.name: dct:created
element.label: Creation date
element.description: Date or range when this object was created.

element.name: dct:creator
element.label: Creator
element.description: An entity responsible for making the resource.

element.name: dct:format
element.label: Format
element.description: The file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource.

element.name: dcat:hasVersion
element.label: Has version

element.name: dct:identifier
element.label: Identifier
element.description: This is the identifier that one can use to refer to this resource, e.g., a URI or other unique identifier within the context of the catalogue. This value, which is predetermined and cannot be changed afterwards, is the UUID for the resource in GeoNetwork. More than one identifier can be added.

element.name: dct:isReferencedBy
element.label: Is referenced by
element.description: A related resource, such as a publication, that references, cites, or otherwise points to the cataloged resource.

element.name: dcat:isVersionOf
element.label: Is a version of
element.description: A related resource of which the described resource is a version, edition, or adaptation.

element.name: dct:issued
element.label: Date issued
element.description: Date of formal issuance of the resource.

element.name: dct:license
element.label: Licence
element.description: A legal document giving official permission to do something with the resource.

element.name: dct:modified
element.label: Date modified
element.description: Date on which the resource was changed.

element.name: dct:provenance
element.label: Provenance
element.description: A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of the resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity and interpretation.

element.name: dct:publisher
element.label: Publisher
element.description: An entity responsible for making the resource available.

element.name: dct:relation
element.label: Related dataset
element.description: A resource with an unspecified relationship to the cataloged item.

element.name: dct:relation
element.label: Related dataset
element.description: A resource with an unspecified relationship to the cataloged item.

element.name: dct:rights
element.label: Rights
element.description: Information about rights held in and over the resource.

element.name: dct:rightsHolder
element.label: Rights holder

element.name: dct:source
element.label: Source
element.description: A related resource from which the described resource is derived.

element.name: dct:title
element.label: Title
element.description: A name given to the resource.

element.name: dct:type
element.label: Type
element.description: The nature or genre of the resource.

element.name: foaf:homepage
element.label: Home page
element.description: URL of the homepage of something, which is a general web resource.

element.name: foaf:workplaceHomepage
element.label: URL
element.description: The Web site of the agent.

element.name: foaf:firstName
element.label: First name
element.description: The first name of the agent.

element.name: foaf:phone
element.label: Phone
element.description: The phone number of the agent, specified using fully qualified tel: URI scheme RFC3966.

element.name: foaf:mbox
element.label: Email
element.description: The email address of the agent, specified using fully qualified mailto: URI scheme RFC6068.

element.name: locn:address
element.label: Address
element.description: An "address representation" as conceptually defined by the INSPIRE Address Representation data type. The locn:addressId property may be used to link this locn:Address to other representations.

element.name: locn:poBox
element.label: PO Box
element.description: The Post Office Box number. The domain of locn:poBox is locn:Address.

element.name: locn:fullAddress
element.label: Full address
element.description: The complete address written as a string, with or without formatting. The domain of locn:fullAddress is locn:Address.

element.name: locn:thoroughfare
element.label: Thoroughfare
element.description: An address component that represents the name of a passage or way through from one location to another. A thoroughfare is not necessarily a road, it might be a waterway or some other feature. The domain of locn:thoroughfare is locn:Address.

element.name: locn:locatorName
element.label: Locator name
element.description: Proper noun(s) applied to the real world entity identified by the locator. The locator name could be the name of the property or complex, of the building or part of the building, or it could be the name of a room inside a building.

element.name: locn:addressArea
element.label: Address area
element.description: The name or names of a geographic area or locality that groups a number of addressable objects for addressing purposes, without being an administrative unit. This would typically be part of a city, a neighbourhood or village. The domain of locn:addressArea is locn:Address.

element.name: locn:postName
element.label: Post name
element.description: The key postal division of the address, usually the city. (INSPIRE's definition is "One or more names created and maintained for postal purposes to identify a subdivision of addresses and postal delivery points."). The domain of locn:postName is locn:Address.

element.name: locn:postCode
element.label: Post code
element.description: The post code (a.k.a postal code, zip code etc.). Post codes are common elements in many countries' postal address systems. The domain of locn:postCode is locn:Address.

element.name: locn:adminUnitL2
element.label: Admin unit L2
element.description: The region of the address, usually a county, state or other such area that typically encompasses several localities. The domain of locn:adminUnitL2 is locn:Address and the range is a literal, conceptually defined by the INSPIRE Geographical Name data type.

element.name: locn:adminUnitL1
element.label: Admin unit L1
element.description: The uppermost administrative unit for the address, almost always a country. The domain of locn:adminUnitL1 is locn:Address and the range is a literal, conceptually defined by the INSPIRE Geographical Name data type.

element.name: locn:locatorDesignator
element.label: Locator designator
element.description: A number or a sequence of characters that uniquely identifies the locator within the relevant scope(s). The full identification of the locator could include one or more locator designators.

element.name: rdf:resource
element.label: Is Version Of

element.name: rdf:resource

element.name: rdf:resource

element.name: rdf:resource
element.label: Download URL
element.description: The URL of the downloadable file in a given format. E.g. CSV file or RDF file. The format is indicated by the distribution's dct:format and/or dcat:mediaType.

element.name: rdf:resource
element.label: Endpoint description
element.description: A description of the services available via the end-points, including their operations, parameters etc.

element.name: rdf:resource

element.label: Landing page

element.name: rdf:resource
element.label: Serves dataset

element.name: skos:Concept
element.label: Concept
element.description: A category or a theme used to describe datasets in the catalog.

element.name: skos:Concept
element.label: Access Rights
element.description: Information about who can access the resource or an indication of its security status.

element.name: dct:hasVersion
element.label: Has version
element.description: A related resource that is a version, edition, or adaptation of the described resource.

element.name: dct:isVersionOf
element.label: Is a version of
element.description: A related resource of which the described resource is a version, edition, or adaptation.

element.name: mobilitydcatap:mobilityTheme
element.label: Mobility theme
element.description: This property refers to the mobility-related theme (i.e., a specific subject, category, or type) of the delivered content. A dataset may be associated with multiple themes. A theme is important for data seekers who are interested in a particular type of data content.

element.name: mobilitydcatap:transportMode
element.label: Transport mode
element.description: This property describes the transport mode that is covered by the delivered content. Data can be valid for more than one mode, so a multiple choice should be applied.

element.name: mobilitydcatap:networkCoverage
element.label: Network coverage
element.description: This property describes the part of the transport network that is covered by the delivered content. For road traffic, the property SHOULD refer to the network classification for which the data is provided. As a minimum, an international or higher-level classification, e.g., via functional road classes, is recommended to allow data search across different countries. In addition, national classifications are allowed. For other transport modes, the property is meant to refer to the physical infrastructure which is used by the services covered by the data. For all modes, the property SHOULD also indicate if the data content relates to the EUs trans-European transport network [EU-TEN-T].

element.name: mobilitydcatap:georeferencingMethod
element.label: Georeferencing method
element.description: This property SHOULD be used to specify the georeferencing method used in the dataset.

element.name: mobilitydcatap:intendedInformationService
element.label: Intended information service
element.description: This property MAY describe predefined information services, which the data content is intended to support. Such services MAY be, e.g., information services for multimodal mobility, as specified by EC Delegated Regulation 2017/1926 [EC-MMTIS-DR]. Examples of such services include location search, which is based on a datasets with address identifiers, or trip plan computation, which is based on datasets about a road network.

element.name: mobilitydcatap:applicationLayerProtocol
element.label: Application layer protocol
element.description: The transmitting channel, i.e., the Application Layer Protocol, of the distribution.

element.name: mobilitydcatap:mobilityDataStandard
element.label: Data standard
element.description: The mobility data standard, as applied for the delivered content within the distribution. A mobility data standard, e.g., DATEX II, combines syntax and semantic definitions of entities in a certain domain (e.g., for DATEX II: road traffic information), and optionally adds technical rules for data exchange.

element.name: mobilitydcatap:schema
element.label: Data standard schema
element.description: The schema of the mobility data standard, as applied within the delivered content. There are different options how to reference the schema. It might be a reference to a portal-internal catalogue of schemas, a reference to an individual schema (that is provided by the data publisher), or a reference to an external catalogue of schemas (like a stakeholder-based DATEX II profile published on the datex2.eu page). The data platform SHOULD keep an archive of commonly used schemas. The data provider SHOULD be able to select an applicable schema from this archive, or to upload an own, individual schema. In any case, the schema should be available as a resource.

element.name: mobilitydcatap:communicationMethod
element.label: Communication method
element.description: Indicates for dynamically provided distributions, e.g., data feeds, if the data interface of the data provider system functions in a push or pull mode.

element.name: mobilitydcatap:grammar
element.label: Technical data grammar format
element.description: The technical data grammar format of the delivered content within the Distribution. It describes the standard on top of the elementary syntax that describe data structures in the dataset.

element.name: mobilitydcatap:assessmentResult
element.label: Assessment result
element.description: The results and outcomes from an assessment process by an external organisation, e.g., a National Body in the context of EU Delegated Regulations. EU Delegated Regulations require Member States to set up procedures to assess the compliance of the Delegated Regulations, e.g. regarding the provisioning of data via a NAP. These assessment processes are handled by National Bodies and installed individually in each Member State. The property may point to the most recent assessment procedure, including its date, its result as a free-text and/or a link referring to an assessment report online.

element.name: mobilitydcatap:dataFormatNotes
element.label: Data format notes
element.description: Any additional information about the format of the delivered content within the distribution in a textual format.

element.name: oa:hasBody
element.label: URL linking to further details or results
element.description: The result of the latest assessment procedure, in form of a URL linking to further details or results. Alternatively, textual information is provided using the Embedded Textual Body construction of the Web Annotation Data Model, which allows to specify text formats and languages which might be relevant for multilingual purposes.

element.name: dqv:hasQualityAnnotation
element.label: Quality annotation
element.description: An annotation about any quality aspects regarding the delivered content, in particular methods, metrics/indicators and results of a quality assessment in the responsibility of the Data Owner.

element.name: cnt:characterEncoding
element.label: Character encoding
element.description: The technical encoding format of the delivered content within the distribution.

element.name: geodcatap:referenceSystem
element.label: Reference system
element.description: The spatial reference system used in the delivered content. To be specified via the EPSG coordinate reference systems register operated by OGC.

element.label: HVD Category
element.description: The HVD category to which this Dataset belongs.

element.name: dcatap:hvdCategory
element.label: HVD Category
element.description: The HVD category to which this Data Service belongs.

element.name: dcatap:hvdCategory
element.label: HVD Category

element.label: Applicable legislation
element.description: The legislation that mandates the creation or management of the Dataset.
